The Postmaster of Mafdet holds an open commission for a complete route survey of the Scorched Wastes. The Wastes are a significant hazard zone on the eastern desert approaches, and the current documentation in the harbor authority's reference files is insufficient for safe expedition planning. Survey every accessible section of the Wastes and return with a complete navigation record.
Your Scorched Wastes survey has been filed with Mafdet's harbor authority. The completed route record is now the primary navigation reference for expeditions operating in the Wastes, and the postmaster has updated the harbor's hazard advisory for the eastern desert approaches accordingly.
